OL,3,CConvicted teacher allowed to continue
OL,4,Cafter holding pupil upside down
OL,6,FThe teacher said he was told by his
OL,7,Fsolicitor that the charge was
OL,8,F"nonsense", and that the case would be
OL,9,Fdropped upon review.
OL,11,FThe panel's investigation concluded
OL,12,Fthat his behaviour was "unacceptable",
OL,13,Fbut decided against banning him from
OL,14,Fthe teaching profession.
OL,16,FA statement by the panel said: "The
OL,17,Fpanel took the view that Mr
OL,18,FHaythornthwaite's conduct was not
OL,19,Fmalicious and was out of character...
OL,20,FThere was no intent by Mr
OL,21,FHaythornthwaite to harm (the pupil).
