OL,3,CConvicted teacher allowed to continue
OL,4,Cafter holding pupil upside down
OL,6,F"Mr Haythornthwaite's behaviour did
OL,7,Fnot lead to a sentence of
OL,8,Fimprisonment, which was indicative
OL,9,Fthat the offence was at the less
OL,10,Fserious end of the possible spectrum.
OL,12,F"I have concluded that a prohibition
OL,13,Forder is not proportionate or in the
OL,14,Fpublic interest."
OL,16,FCumberland Council has been approached
OL,17,Ffor comment.
